      "instruction": "<p>Take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air, then boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely dice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong>, then heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 3-5 min or until beginning to soften</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1678987684554-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1678987684554-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1678987684554-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1678987684554-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1678987684554-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the onion is softening, peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>ginger </strong>and <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Bash your <strong>lemongrass</strong> with a <strong>rolling pin</strong></p><p>Chop the <strong>softer inner core</strong> finely</p><p>Remove the <strong>tough outer layers</strong> of the lemongrass and set aside for later</p><p>Slice half your<strong> red chilli[es]</strong> into rounds and finely chop the remaining</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1678987688653-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1678987688653-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1678987688653-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1678987688653-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1678987688653-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has softened, add the <strong>chopped ginger </strong>and<strong> garlic</strong>, <strong>chopped lemongrass</strong>, <strong>chopped chilli </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and <strong>bay leaf[ves] </strong>to the pan and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>diced chicken thigh</strong>, <strong>half </strong>your <strong>cider vinegar </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) and a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 2-3 min or until starting to brown</p><p>While the chicken is browning, rinse your <strong>red lentils</strong> in a sieve under <strong>cold running water</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1678987693842-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1678987693842-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1678987693842-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1678987693842-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1678987693842-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop your <strong>creamed</strong> <strong>coconut</strong> (if required!), then dissolve your <strong>chicken stock mix </strong>and <strong>chopped creamed coconut </strong>in 500ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[650ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\">[850ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>– this is your <strong>coconut stock</strong></p><p>Once the chicken is starting to brown, add your <strong>tomato paste</strong>, <strong>rinsed lentils</strong> and <strong>coconut stock </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium-low and cook, covered, for an initial 18-20 min or until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1678987703494-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1678987703494-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1678987703494-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1678987703494-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1678987703494-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>white long grain rice</strong>, <strong>outer lemongrass</strong> <strong>layers </strong>and<strong> </strong>175ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[230ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[350ml] </span><strong>cold water</strong> to a pot with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once cooked, remove from the heat and keep covered until serving – this is your <strong>lemongrass rice</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1678987708597-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1678987708597-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1678987708597-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1678987708597-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1678987708597-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the rice is cooking, add the<strong> chilli rounds</strong> to a bowl with the <strong>remaining cider vinegar</strong>, 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp] </span><strong>sugar</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and set aside to pickle – this is your <strong>quick-pickled chilli</strong></p><p>Wash your <strong>spinach</strong> and pat it dry with kitchen paper</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1678987712934-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1678987712934-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1678987712934-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1678987712934-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1678987712934-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>After an initial 20 min, add the <strong>spinach </strong>to the pan and cook, uncovered, for a further 2-3 min or until the spinach has wilted and the sauce has thickened slightly – this is your <strong>Filipino-style chicken & lentil curry</strong></p><p>Discard the bay leaf[ves]</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1678987717764-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1678987717764-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1678987717764-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1678987717764-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1678987717764-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>Filipino-style chicken & lentil curry</strong> over the <strong>lemongrass rice </strong>(discard the lemongrass!)</p><p>Garnish with the <strong>quick-pickled chilli</strong> (not a fan of spice? Just add a little!)</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
